<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="1221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1221">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812,512/295.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-26T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Consul, Tampico, reports that customs authorities are forcing oil
                            companies to pay taxes Mexican gold, or American gold at two for one
                            when exchange is three for one, and that they refuse to accept
                            Carrancista currency bills although these made legal tender by decrees
                            April 1913 and February 1914.</p>
                        <p>Bring to attention of Carranza and request that orders be given for
                            relief from this manifestly unjust action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>